# MVW Phase 2 - Consolidated Planning List

**Last Updated:** November 9, 2025

**Deployment Strategy:** Phase 2 MVW will be built as a complete package in staging environment, then deployed as one release.

---

## Category A: Hero Components & Above-the-Fold Refinements

**Priority: HIGH** - Affects first impression across multiple templates

1. Hero ATF: Reduce height to better fit 16:9 viewports
2. Hero ATF: Update all above-the-fold components to account for combined header height
3. Hero simple/reverse: Fix resizing issues
4. Hero simple reverse: Change gradient orientation in banner
5. Buttons: Regularize all button state definitions
   - Hero ATF Centered
   - Main Footer

**Dependencies:** None - can be tackled early in Phase 2

---

## Category B: Navigation & Interaction Refinements

**Priority: HIGH** - Critical for UX across all pages

### B1: Sticky Menu System
1. Reduce minimum tablet width to 768px
2. Fix sticky behavior in DesktopPlus

### B2: Animation & Timing
1. Header nav menu dropdown: Open smoother and slower (tablet and mobile)
2. Footer mobile menu accordion: Smoother and slower animation

### B3: Interactive Elements
1. Return button: Expand bounding box area for better clickability

**Dependencies:** None - standalone improvements

---

## Category C: Homepage Carousel Updates

**Priority: MEDIUM** - Content refresh and interaction refinement

1. Replace carousel slide 2 with different stock video (mp4)
2. Carousel overlay button: Decide whether to keep current state behavior or update to match v4.0 variables definition

**Dependencies:** None - can be done anytime

---

## Category D: Section Layout & Spacing Refinements

**Priority: MEDIUM** - Visual polish and consistency

1. FAQ section: Background adjustment
2. Next step section: Reduce background height by ~10%
3. Next step graphic 2-column: Adjust height or bottom alignment to show stock model's face in cards

**Dependencies:** None - standalone visual refinements

---

## Category E: Contact & Form System Improvements

**Priority: HIGH** - Affects lead capture functionality

1. Contact Us section: Reformat to 2 columns + CTA layout
2. Contact form: Fix success statement message
3. Footer newsletter sign-up: Fix success statement message

**Dependencies:** Items 2-3 depend on item 1 completion for consistent form messaging

---

## Category F: Blog System Enhancements

**Priority: HIGH** - Core content delivery mechanism

1. Blog page: Add headline banner above blog component
2. Blog page: Connect blog posts and activate infinite scroll/pagination
3. Blog page: Add linking between related content

**Dependencies:** Item 1 is independent. Items 2-3 require WordPress functionality (see Category J)

---

## Category G: New Templates (Phase 2 Core)

**Priority: HIGH** - Required for Phase 2 operations

1. Blog post template: Design and build (individual post layout)
2. Landing page template: Design and build (lead generation)
3. Resource Offer page template: Design and build (eBook downloads)
4. Email template: Design and build (HubSpot integration)

**Dependencies:**
- Template 4 (Email) blocks Category H (Email System Integration)
- Template 3 (Resource Offer) needed for Category I item 1 (PDF resources)

---

## Category H: Email System Integration

**Priority: HIGH** - Required for lead nurturing

1. HubSpot email configuration
2. Write initial onboarding email sequence
3. Implement onboarding sequence in HubSpot

**Dependencies:**
- Requires Category G item 4 (Email template) to be completed first
- Item 2 blocks item 3

---

## Category I: Content Creation & Publishing (Non-Development)

**Priority: HIGH** - Blocks lead generation

1. Publish PDF resources:
   - 4 eBooks
   - 3 case studies
   - 1 capabilities deck
2. eBook disclaimer section: Write copy (factual accuracy statement and contact info for broken links)
3. Finalize eBook versions:
   - Upwork version
   - External publication version with contact information

**Dependencies:**
- Item 1 requires Category G item 3 (Resource Offer template) to be completed
- Item 2 blocks finalization of eBooks in item 3

---

## Category J: WordPress Functionality Enhancements

**Priority: HIGH** - Needed for blog and content features

1. Blog page: Connect posts with infinite scroll/pagination functionality
2. Add linking system between related content across site

**Dependencies:**
- Item 1 blocks Category F items 2-3 (Blog system enhancements)
- Item 2 enhances overall site UX after content pages are added

---

## Category K: Future Content Pages (Expansion)

**Priority: MEDIUM** - Enhancement, not blocker

### Pillar Pages (Template assembly + copy)
1. Succession Planning pillar page
2. Business Unit Growth pillar page

### Topic Pages (Template assembly + copy)
3. Revenue Growth topic page
4. Preparing for Exit topic page
5. Plan a Webinar topic page
6. Pricing topic page
7. Affiliates topic page

**Dependencies:** All items require completed content copy before page assembly

---

## Implementation Notes

### Critical Path (Must complete in order):
1. Category G item 4 (Email template) → Category H (Email system)
2. Category G item 3 (Resource Offer template) → Category I item 1 (Publish PDFs)
3. Category I item 2 (eBook disclaimer) → Category I item 3 (Finalize eBooks)
4. Category H item 2 (Write email sequence) → Category H item 3 (Implement sequence)
5. Category J item 1 (Blog functionality) → Category F items 2-3 (Blog enhancements)

### Can Work in Parallel:
- Category A (Hero components)
- Category B (Navigation)
- Category C (Homepage carousel)
- Category D (Section spacing)
- Category E (Contact/forms)
- Category F item 1 (Blog headline banner)

### Content-Dependent (Requires copy/assets):
- Category I (PDF resources and eBook finalization)
- Category K (All future pages)
- Category H item 2 (Email sequence writing)

---

## Phase 2 Deployment Checklist

Before moving Phase 2 MVW from staging to production:

- [ ] All Category A-E refinements complete and tested
- [ ] All Category G templates built and validated
- [ ] Category H email system configured and tested
- [ ] Category I resources published and accessible
- [ ] Category J WordPress functionality tested
- [ ] Cross-browser testing complete (Chrome, Firefox, Safari)
- [ ] Responsive testing at all 4 breakpoints (Mobile, Tablet, Desktop, DesktopPlus)
- [ ] W3C validation passed for new templates
- [ ] Form submissions tested and success messages verified
- [ ] HubSpot integration tested end-to-end
- [ ] Category K pages added (as ready with copy)

---

